 CAPS United Skipper Hardlife Zvirekwi was involved in a car crash early Monday morning along Samora Machel Avenue. According to a press statement released by CAPS United, Zvirekwi who is admitted at Parirenyatwa hospital is said to be in a stable but critical condition. The statement reads: “We Would like to sadly advise the nation, the sporting fraternity and all our valued stakeholders that our Captain, Hardlife Zvirekwi was involved in a serious accident early this morning and we thank God he survived though with severe injuries. “His condition is critical, and the extent of injuries and implication on his playing career will be confirmed in due course after some medical examinations. Hardlife Zvirekwi is currently hospitalised and receiving treatment.” Sportszone 